William Woodruff
Professor John Beckett writes:
Your obituary of William Woodruff (died 25 September) states that "in 1946 he had resumed his studies in economic history in Oxford, and in 1950 became a member of Houblon-Norma research, while doing a BSc, MA, and PhD".
That's what came from Woodruff's letter in Beyond Nab End, but that's not correct.
From 1946 to 1953 he was a professor of economic history at the University of Nottingham, and at the same time completed a PhD thesis on the British plastic industry, under the supervision of Professor J.D. Chambers; it was later published in 1958 as The British Rubber Industry.
